Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper deals with indoor localization, which is a subfield of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper discusses a system that can be used for tracking the location of multiple agents (i.e., people or devices) in an indoor environment. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a system for controlling the location of devices in an indoor environment. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of FM radio signals for indoor localization, which involves the transmission and processing of information. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of FM radio signals for indoor localization, which involves the processing of audio signals.
